THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 277 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. If a tribal government wishes to enter into an agreement
4 for joint or cooperative action or contract with the governing body
5 of a county or agency thereof, pursuant to the provisions of this
6 section and NRS 277.080 to 277.180, inclusive, within which tribal
7 land of the tribal government is located, partially or wholly, for the
8 performance of any governmental service, activity or undertaking
9 which the tribal government, county or agency thereof is
10 authorized by law to perform, the governing body of the county
11 shall, on behalf of the county or agency thereof, engage in
12 discussions in good faith with the tribal government for the
13 performance of such services.
14 2. If the governing body of a county or agency thereof enters
15 into an agreement or contract pursuant to the provisions of this
16 section and NRS 277.080 to 277.180, inclusive, such an agreement
17 must be a conditional interlocal agreement which:
18 (a) Must not require a tribal government to waive sovereign
19 immunity; and
20 (b) Must authorize the governing body of the county or agency
21 thereof to terminate the agreement by providing the tribal
22 government with 90 days’ advance written notice, upon the
23 occurrence of any of the following conditions:
24 (1) The tribal government is more than 60 days delinquent
25 on its financial obligations under the agreement;
26 (2) The tribal government fails to respond for more than 90
27 days to a written demand by the governing body of the county or
28 agency thereof to perform under the agreement;
29 (3) An authorized representative of the tribal government
30 or tribal council or tribal police of the tribal government prevents
31 entry onto the tribal land or otherwise prevents the county or
32 agency thereof, or any employee or agent of the county or agency,
33 from otherwise performing under the agreement; or
34 (4) The tribal government enters into any subsequent
35 agreement pursuant to this section and NRS 277.080 to 277.180,
36 inclusive, which materially conflicts with the existing agreement.
37 3. As used in this section, “tribal government” means the
38 governing body of an Indian tribe, group of tribes, organized
